label: A20B3_cI184_204_def3gh_g-001
title: YCd$_{6}$ Structure
comments:
The site we label Cd-VI is occupied only 33.1\% of the time.  Removing this atom transforms this to the \href{current_web_home_dir/A17B3_cI160_204_def2gh_g-001}{Ru$_{3}$Be$_{17}$ structure}. 
 (Armbr\"{u}ster, 2000) found that what had previously been thought to be CeCd$_{6}$ was actually \href{current_web_home_dir/A41B6_cP188_201_b2efg5h_h-001}{Ce$_{6}$Cd$_{37}$}.  This suggests that other XCd$_{6}$ structures may actually have different compositions. 
 (Armbr\"{u}ster, 2000) also give a structure for CeCd$_{6}$ which differs slightly from the one presented here.
